HEADWORD: Quatorze
<hw>Qua*torze"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>quatorze</ets> fourteen, L. <ets>quattuordecim</ets>. See
<er>Fourteen</er>.]</ety> <def>The four aces, kings, queens, knaves, or
tens, in the game of piquet; -- so called because <xex>quatorze</xex>
counts as fourteen points.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quatrain</ent>⟦br⟧
